## Data Types

### Preferred Types
| Use Case | PostgreSQL Type | Notes |
|----------|----------------|-------|
| Primary key | `UUID DEFAULT gen_random_uuid()` | Never serial/auto-increment |
| Foreign key | `UUID REFERENCES table(id)` | Always add index |
| Timestamps | `TIMESTAMPTZ` | Always with timezone |
| Short text | `TEXT` with CHECK constraint | `CHECK (char_length(username) <= 30)` |
| Long text | `TEXT` | No artificial limits unless needed |
| Boolean | `BOOLEAN NOT NULL DEFAULT false` | Always set default |
| Count | `INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 0` | Never nullable for counts |
| Enum | Custom `ENUM` type | For fixed value sets |
| JSON data | `JSONB` | Only for truly dynamic data |

### Rules
- Prefer specific types over `TEXT` or `JSONB` when the shape is known.
- Always add `NOT NULL` with a `DEFAULT` unless the column is genuinely optional.
- Use `CHECK` constraints for validation (string length, numeric ranges).
- Use `UNIQUE` constraints where business logic requires it.

## Seed Data

### Format
```sql
-- supabase/seed.sql
-- Development seed data — only run in local/staging environments

-- Seed categories
INSERT INTO public.categories (id, slug, name_tr, icon, sort_order) VALUES
  (gen_random_uuid(), 'movies', 'Filmler', '🎬', 1),
  (gen_random_uuid(), 'music', 'Müzik', '🎵', 2),
  (gen_random_uuid(), 'food', 'Yemek', '🍕', 3),
  (gen_random_uuid(), 'travel', 'Seyahat', '✈️', 4),
  (gen_random_uuid(), 'hobbies', 'Hobiler', '🎮', 5)
ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING;
```

### Rules
- Seed data is for development only.
- Use `ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING` to make seeds re-runnable.
- Never include production secrets or real user data.
- Include enough data to test all features.

## Performance

### Query Optimization
- Always specify columns in `SELECT` — never `SELECT *`.
- Add indexes on columns used in `WHERE`, `JOIN`, `ORDER BY`.
- Use `EXPLAIN ANALYZE` to verify query plans.
- Paginate: default `LIMIT 20`, max `LIMIT 100`.
- Use `maybeSingle()` on the client when a row might not exist.

### Connection Pooling
- Use PgBouncer connection pooling in production (port 6543).
- Transaction mode for serverless environments.
- Session mode only when needed (prepared statements, advisory locks).

## Backup & Recovery
- Supabase managed backups for production.
- Test restore procedures before launch.
- Point-in-time recovery enabled for production project.
